# Copy this file to .env.local. Never commit .env.local.
#
# Required to run the dashboard:
# NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL=http://localhost:3000
#
# GitHub OAuth sign-in (configure the GitHub OAuth App credentials in Supabase Dashboard,
# not in this file). In Supabase Auth, enable GitHub and add these redirect URLs:
#   http://localhost:3000/auth/callback
#   https://<your-vercel-domain>/auth/callback
# GitHub's OAuth callback must be the Supabase callback shown in its GitHub provider screen:
#   https://<project-ref>.supabase.co/auth/v1/callback
# The application uses the new publishable Supabase key below for the browser OAuth flow.
# ACCESSAGENT_REQUIRE_AUTH=true
#
# AI provider selection. OpenAI is the production default; omit this line or set it to
# openai to run strictly on OpenAI. Set it to gemini only for the isolated test provider.
# ACCESSAGENT_AI_PROVIDER=openai
#
# Required for visual audit and verification with OpenAI (the default):
# Create an API key in your OpenAI project and add it here. The key stays server-side.
# OPENAI_API_KEY=
# Lower-cost default suitable for the hackathon proof. Override either with
# gpt-5.4 later if you want the higher-capability production model.
# OPENAI_VISION_MODEL=gpt-5-mini
# OPENAI_PATCH_MODEL=gpt-5-mini
#
# Optional Gemini testing provider. Add these to the Render worker only when
# ACCESSAGENT_AI_PROVIDER=gemini. Do not paste a Gemini key into OPENAI_API_KEY.
# Free-tier Gemini data may be used by Google to improve its products; use only
# the included demo target or another non-sensitive site you own or may test.
# GEMINI_API_KEY=
# GEMINI_VISION_MODEL=gemini-3.5-flash
# GEMINI_PATCH_MODEL=gemini-3.5-flash
# For a Gemini proof run, set these in Vercel too so the dashboard queues only
# one page and keeps image and DOM evidence bounded:
# ACCESSAGENT_MAX_PAGES=1
# ACCESSAGENT_MAX_DEPTH=0
#
# Required for isolated, untrusted agent patch execution (Vercel Sandbox):
# In production on Vercel this is supplied automatically via OIDC. For local development,
# run `vercel link` followed by `vercel env pull` to obtain a development token.
# VERCEL_OIDC_TOKEN=
#
# Required for durable audit → patch → verify workflows and live traces (Inngest):
# INNGEST_EVENT_KEY=
# INNGEST_SIGNING_KEY=
#
# Required for run history, Realtime dashboard updates, and screenshot evidence (Supabase):
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=
# In Supabase Dashboard: Project Settings > API Keys, create/copy a Publishable key.
# This is safe to expose in a browser when Row Level Security is enabled.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=
#
# In Supabase Dashboard: Project Settings > API Keys, create/copy a Secret key.
# It bypasses Row Level Security. Keep it server-only: never prefix it with NEXT_PUBLIC_,
# never commit it, and never paste it into chat.
# SUPABASE_SECRET_KEY=
#
# Required only when you enable patching against a repository:
# GitHub repository URL for Vercel Sandbox to clone. AccessAgent creates a new
# temporary accessagent/... branch automatically; it never pushes to main.
# ACCESSAGENT_REPO_URL=
# The sandbox starts with no node_modules, so install before testing.
# ACCESSAGENT_TEST_COMMAND=npm ci --legacy-peer-deps && npm run test
# Required before a PR can be opened: commits the stored before/after screenshots to
# the temporary AccessAgent branch so they appear in the GitHub PR. Enable only when
# the target page may be represented in the repository's visibility scope.
# ACCESSAGENT_PUBLISH_PR_EVIDENCE=true
#
# Required only when you enable pull-request creation:
# Create a GitHub fine-grained token with Contents: Read/Write and Pull requests: Read/Write.
# GITHUB_TOKEN=
# GITHUB_OWNER=
# GITHUB_REPO=
# GITHUB_BASE_BRANCH=main
#
# Required for Vercel connected-Git preview lookup after the sandbox pushes a branch.
# AccessAgent finds the new branch preview automatically; do not set a localhost URL.
# VERCEL_TOKEN=
# VERCEL_PROJECT_ID=
# VERCEL_TEAM_ID=
#
# Optional operational limits for a demo run:
# ACCESSAGENT_MAX_PAGES=5
# ACCESSAGENT_MAX_DEPTH=2
# ACCESSAGENT_MAX_ATTEMPTS=3
# ACCESSAGENT_AUDITS_PER_HOUR=5
# ACCESSAGENT_RETENTION_DAYS=30
# Optional incident webhook for failed workflow alerts:
# ACCESSAGENT_ALERT_WEBHOOK_URL=
#
# Deploy the dashboard, Inngest handlers, and Vercel Sandbox control plane to Vercel.
#
# Browser worker deployment (Render):
# The Vercel app remains the dashboard/API. Deploy this same repository to Render
# as a Docker Web Service using Dockerfile, then sync Inngest to:
#   https://<your-render-worker>.onrender.com/api/inngest
# Copy the server-side values above into Render. In particular, Render needs
# VERCEL_TOKEN, VERCEL_PROJECT_ID, and VERCEL_TEAM_ID so it can create the
# existing Vercel Sandbox without Vercel's automatic OIDC token.
